\maketitle

\begin{abstract}
This report presents the modelling, linearisation, and controller design 
for a nonlinear electromechanical system consisting of a wooden ball on 
an inclined plane actuated by an electromagnet. The objective is to 
design a controller capable of stabilising the system near 
$x_{sp} = 0.4\,\text{m}$ while ensuring BIBO stability, zero steady-state 
error, and disturbance rejection.
\end{abstract}

