\section{Nonlinear System Modelling}

\subsection{Mechanical Dynamics}

Derive Newton’s second law along the incline:

\begin{equation}
m\ddot{x} = \text{(forces along incline)}
\end{equation}

Include:
\begin{itemize}
    \item Gravity component
    \item Spring force
    \item Damping force
    \item Magnetic force
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Electrical Dynamics}

From circuit analysis:

\begin{equation}
V = Ri + \frac{d}{dt}(L(x)i)
\end{equation}

Include inductance expression and magnetic force equation.

\subsection{Sensor Model}

First-order sensor model:

\begin{equation}
\tau_m \dot{y} + y = x
\end{equation}

\subsection{State-Space Representation}

Define state vector:

\begin{equation}
\mathbf{x} =
\begin{bmatrix}
x \\
\dot{x} \\
i \\
y
\end{bmatrix}
\end{equation}

Define input:

\[
u = V
\]

Write nonlinear system:

\begin{equation}
\dot{\mathbf{x}} = f(\mathbf{x},u)
\end{equation}

\begin{equation}
y = g(\mathbf{x},u)
\end{equation}

\section{Linearisation Around Operating Point}

Linearise about:

\[
x = x_{sp} = 0.4\,\text{m}
\]

Present Jacobian matrices:

\begin{equation}
\dot{\mathbf{x}} = A\mathbf{x} + B u
\end{equation}

\begin{equation}
y = C\mathbf{x} + D u
\end{equation}

